<h2>About The Artist</h2>
<body>
<img src="file:///Users/sophiaprice/Desktop/ProfilePicture.jpeg" alt="Profile Picture">
</body>
<p>
Sophia Price, born in Hudson, Ohio started her music and songwriting journey at the age of 12 teaching herself how to play guitar and piano. She began performing at local coffee shops and community music festivals when she was 15, and then later attended <strong>Interlochen Arts Academy</strong> in Michigan where she received intensive singing and songwriting training. After being fully self taught in guitar, piano, bass, and classically trained on flute, she then took her talents to New Orleans Louisiana where she now studies at <strong>Loyola University</strong> where she has collaborated in writing with numerous other artists <strong> (<em>Lyla DiPaul, Thea Aksland, Michael Sparks</em>)</strong> as well as performed around the New Orleans area. Primarily a pop writer, her musical influences consists of Hozier, Pheobe Bridgers, Billie Eilish, Briston Maroney, Taylor Swift, and Lorde. In every show, Price would like to give a shoutout to her family and friends for their continued love and support as she embarks in her career. </p>
</main>
<h2>Be On The Look Out!</h2>
